ray.rage.asset.mesh

Class Mesh

  • java.lang.Object
    • ray.rage.asset.AbstractAsset
      • ray.rage.asset.mesh.Mesh
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Asset, Disposable, Managed<AssetManager<? extends Asset>>, Nameable

    public final class Mesh
extends AbstractAsset
    A mesh is an asset holding data about a discrete 3-dimensional object. This class is not intended (or appropriate) for large-scale sprawling geometry found in 'static' level data (e.g. terrains, the world itself, etc).

    Mesh data usually has more than just vertex and triangle information. This can include references to materials, animations, and other things. Multiple world objects can (and should) be created from a single mesh object.

    Meshes are split into sub-meshes and have a 1:M relationship, because different parts of a mesh may use different materials, which may require rendering state changes. Meshes also have a 1:M relationship with entities, where each mesh may be shared by one or more entities.

    Author:
    Raymond L. Rivera
    See Also:
    SubMesh, Entity

        public SubMesh createSubMesh(java.lang.String name)
        Creates a new sub-mesh with this mesh as the parent.

        This method should be used carefully, as it allows the manual definition of geometry. If used for this purpose, make sure you've correctly defined the geometry.

        Parameters:
        name - The name for the sub-mesh.
        Returns:
        The new sub-mesh.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the name is empty.
